    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46), an uncompromising example of Bavarian engineering. This specimen features the S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies and high-pressure double-VANOS, providing a 7,900 RPM redline and surgical throttle response. Power is delivered through a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a GKN-visco-lok limited-slip differential. The chassis is structurally flawless; the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced, and the rod bearing service is documented. The suspension retains original geometry with no bushing deflection or damper fatigue. Finished in Carbon Black Metallic with a pristine Nappa leather interior, the vehicle displays factory-spec panel gaps and zero paint degradation. A turn-key investment for the discerning collector.",
